premise_source_doc_sentence: Mount Mitchell is the highest peak of the Appalachian Mountains and the highest peak in mainland eastern North America .
It is located near Burnsville in Yancey County , North Carolina , in the Black Mountain subrange of the Appalachians , and about 19 mi northeast of Asheville .
It is protected by Mount Mitchell State Park and surrounded by the Pisgah National Forest .
Mount Mitchell 's elevation is 6684 ft above sea level .
